<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <base href="/" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="_content/Radzen.Blazor/css/standard-base.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="app.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="ClaudeWorkbench.Host.styles.css" />
    <ImportMap />
    @* Two icon links on purpose.

       favicon.ico is listed first and also sits at the site root, because a browser running this in
       app-window mode asks for /favicon.ico directly and may never read these <link> tags at all --
       which is why replacing only favicon.png left the app window still showing the old mark.

       The ?v= is a cache-buster. Favicons are cached far more aggressively than pages, and an app
       window caches its icon per-profile, so a plain Ctrl+F5 does not necessarily refresh it. Bump
       the version whenever the icon changes. *@
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="favicon.ico?v=2" sizes="any" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="favicon.png?v=2" />
    <title>ClaudeWorkbench</title>
    <HeadOutlet @rendermode="InteractiveServer" />
</head>

<body>
    <Routes @rendermode="InteractiveServer" />
    <script src="_content/Radzen.Blazor/Radzen.Blazor.js"></script>
    @* Mermaid, vendored locally (no CDN) so ```mermaid fences render inline as diagrams.
       The bundle sets window.mermaid; sourceResize.js initializes it lazily on first use. *@
    <script src="lib/mermaid/mermaid.min.js"></script>
    <script src="_framework/blazor.web.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
